Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Zest the @lemon{1}, then juice one half. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Cut the @Persian cucumber{1} into ¾-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}. Halve the @black olives{1%ounce} and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Finely chop the @oregano{1/4%ounce}(leaves only). Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%box}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the cannellini beans and garlic and cook, tossing until the garlic is fragrant, for ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the lemon zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Toast the pitas: Cut the @whole wheat pitas{2} into thin strips. Place the strips onto a #baking sheet{} and drizzle with @olive oil{4%tsp}. Place in the oven for about ~{5%minutes}, until slightly crispy.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the oregano, lemon juice, @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} and a large drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss the cucumber, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, tomatoes, cannellini beans, olives, and red onion (to taste) into the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Enjoy: Serve the chopped Greek salad with the toasted pita on top and dig in!